Nigeria will clash with Sudan in a 2021 Africa Cup of Nations, AFCON, tie on Saturday evening. The 2021 AFCON match will take place at the Roumdé Adjia Stadium, Garoua, in Cameroon. Nigeria and Sudan are in Group D, alongside Egypt and Guinea-Bissau. The Super Eagles defeated Egypt 1-0 on Tuesday, thanks to Kelechi Iheanacho’s first-half goal, while the Falcons of Jediane played a 0-0 draw against Guinea-Bissau. Nigeria’s starting XI: Okoye, Aina, Troost-Ekong, Omeruo, Sanusi, Aribo, Ndidi, Chukwueze, Simon, Iheanacho and Awoniyi. Sudan’s starting XI: Alshareif Eisa, Omer Yagoub, Hamed, Abbas Omer, Shambaly, W.K, Saeed Elfadni, Nemer, Karshoum, Alnour Mohamed and Eshrein. Full Time: Nigeria 3 – 1 Sudan (Samuel Chukwueze 3, Taiwo Awoniyi 45, Moses Simon 46) , Walieldin Khedr (P) 70